                      ALMOND MONITORING DAEMON SOURCE INSTALLATION

____________________________________________________________________________________________________

1. PREREQUISITES
   In order to run the install script you need to have a c compiler, make and automake installed.
   - gcc
   - make
   - automake

   For the default plugins to work you also need to have the following installed:
   - ksh
   - sysstat
   - python3
   - perl
   - python3-psutil (pip3 install psutil)
   - ping
   - ps

2. RUN THE INSTALL SCRIPT
   Run the script ./install_almond.sh

   This script will compile and install Almond monitoring daemon and copy initial configuration and
   plugin files.

   To just compile almond with the correct dependecies installed you write:
   gcc main.c -lpthread -ljson-c -o almond

   To compile almond with support for kafka_exports you run:
   gcc main.c mod_kafka.c -lpthread -ljson-c -lrdkafka -lz -o almond

3. START THE ALMOND PROCESS
   After running the install script you can start Almond with the following command:
   
   /opt/almond/start_almond.sh

4. PLUGIN NOTICE
   Some plugins installed by default will have their own prerequisites such as Python and Perl with
   additional modules. Some plugins are binary and compiled under x86_64/amd64 for Debian and if
   they are not working you need to download/install/compile them for the distribution and or
   architecture where you want to run the Almond software.
